{
  "texts": [
    "The data in the problem are µ ∈ R n, the vector of expected asset returns, and Σ, the n × n covariance matrix of asset returns.",
    "The positive parameter σ tar is the target portfolio return standard deviation or volatility.",
    "(We define the weights and describe the problem more carefully in §2.)",
    "There are many other ways to formulate the trade-off of expected return and risk as an optimization problem [BV04, ApS23].",
    "One very popular method maximizes the risk-adjusted return, which is the expected portfolio return minus its variance, scaled by a positive riskaversion parameter."
  ]
}